pango1.0
------------------------------------------
Pango is a library for layout and rendering of text, with an emphasis
on internationalization. Pango can be used anywhere that text layout
is needed; however, most of the work on Pango so far has been done using
the GTK+ widget toolkit as a test platform. Pango forms the core of text
and font handling for GTK+-2.x.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.5-1
  libcairo2-1.8.10-1
  libfontconfig1-2.8.0-1
  libfreetype6-2.3.12-1
  libgcc1-4.3.4-3
  libglib2.0_0-2.24.1-1
  libX11_6-1.3.3-1
  libXft2-2.1.14-1
  libXrender1-0.9.5-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf2.5-2.65-1
  automake1.11-1.11.1-1
  binutils-2.20.51-2
  cygport-0.9.85-1
  gawk-3.1.7-1
  gcc4-core-4.3.4-3
  gnome-common-2.28.0-2
  gobject-introspection-0.6.14-1
  gtk-doc-1.15-1
  help2man-1.36.4-11
  libtool-2.2.7a-15
  make-3.81-2
  pkg-config-0.23b-10

Canonical website:
  http://www.pango.org/

Canonical download:
  ftp://ftp.gnome.org/pub/gnome/sources/pango/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack pango1.0-1.28.1-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./pango1.0-1.28.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/girepository-Pango1.0-1.28.1-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libpango1.0_0-1.28.1-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libpango1.0-devel-1.28.1-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/pango1.0-1.28.1-X-src.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

